data.stimulus:
Welcome

Welcome to the Experiment! In this experiment, we will give you one anagram to solve. An anagram is simply a word or phrase formed by rearranging the letters of another word or phrase. For example:

  • POKER is an anagram of PKOER
  • PHONE is an anagram of POEHN

We kindly request for your full attention for the experiment and ask you to refrain from using Google or other search engines.

Please press the 'n' key to continue once you understand.

Instructions

When you click next, you will be presented with an anagram that will be displayed for 4 seconds. Following that, the same anagram will be presented to you again in a different configuration for 4 seconds. This will be repeated multiple times and your goal is to solve the anagram by the end of the experiment.

As an example, you may be presented with random configurations such as: ONLEM, MOELN, and NMEOL. Here, these configurations come from the same anagram, LEMON and your goal was figuring out the underlying anagram.

Please press the 'm' key to continue once you understand.

Instructions

Now, we will present you the anagram which you have to solve. We will present the anagram to you in various different configurations. Please try your best to solve the anagram.

Please press the 'b' key to continue.
OCRAIGN
Now we will show you another configuration of the anagram
CROAIGN
Now we will show you another configuration of the anagram
NACGIOR
Now we will show you another configuration of the anagram
ORAGNIC
Now we will show you another configuration of the anagram
